commText: Rohit and Ishan Kishan are at the crease. Rohit is on strike. Bhuvneshwar will open the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Rohit, no run, gentle outswinger outside off, Rohit waits and pats it with soft hands to point
Bhuvneshwar to Rohit, FOUR, Rohit has had a sighter. Sees a fullish delivery around off and just swings through the line, lofts it straight back over and collects a one bounce four
Bhuvneshwar to Rohit, 1 run, short and outside off, Rohit cracks it firmly but straight to sweeper cover
Rohit is playing his 200th game for Mumbai today and he was presented a special jersey by Sachin Tendulkar. Mumbai will hope he makes it a memorable day
Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, no run, back of a length and bit of extra bounce, Kishan rides the bounce and pats it to the on-side

Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, leg byes, FOUR, wrong line from Bhuvi. Strays down leg, Kishan misses the heave and the ball deflects off the thigh pad to the right of Klaasen. He dives and parries it to the fence
Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, no run, back of a length around off, Kishan checks his punch and picks out cover-point
Jaydev Unadkat, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Unadkat to Rohit, 1 run, short of length close to off, Rohit drops it with soft hands behind the wicket and Kishan quickly crosses over

Unadkat to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, low full toss around off, Kishan punches it straight down the ground, Unadkat sticks out his left leg and deflects it to the right of mid-on. It was struck well enough for the ball to travel the distance
Unadkat to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, good length ball around off, Kishan ekes out an inside edge onto the pad and the ball rolls into the off-side
Unadkat to Rohit, SIX, fabulous shot! Unadkat is a too straight - on middle and leg, Rohit gets inside the line and helps it along the way over backward square, just clears the rope

Unadkat to Rohit, SIX, back to back the sixes. Rohit gives the charge, makes a bit of room and that allows him to have a free swing of the hands against the back of a length delivery, launched over deep mid-wicket
Unadkat to Rohit, no run, I0$ yorker around off, Rohit makes room and squeezes it straight to backward point
Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, streaky! But Kishan and Mumbai won't be complaining. He swings across the line and gets a thick top-edge over short third, the ball bounces just inside the rope
Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, SIX, that's off the middle and into the stands. Fraction short and Kishan is quick to latch on, he rocks back and nails the pull over deep square leg

Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, SIX, six more.. Bhuvi goes for the slower ball - I0$ but right in the slot, Kishan brings his bottom hand into play and whips it over cow corner. Another six that just clears the rope but gets the nod of approval from Rohit
Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, no run, yorker outside off, Ishan fails to dig it out

Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, SIX, third six in the over. Full pitcher and Kishan lofts straight down the ground, 81 meter six and even an experienced campaigner from Bhuvi can't do much on this belter
Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, 50 up for Mumbai. Just the start they needed. Bhuvi manages to nail the yorker on the stumps, Kishan digs it to long-on and retains strike
Shahbaz Ahmed, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Shahbaz Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, SIX, this is a brave move from Cummins - bowling Shahbaz to the left hander. Darted across from round the wicket, Kishan sits down and launches it into the second tier at deep mid-wicket
Shahbaz Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Shahbaz Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Markram!! And the move pays off. SRH owner - Kavya Maran - breathes a sign of relief. This was drifted across the left hander and Kishan decided to repeat the slog sweep, does not get it off the middle and the ball skies towards deep mid-wicket, Markram settles under it and takes it calmly. Kishan might have done his job of getting Mumbai off to a flier. Ishan Kishan c Markram b Shahbaz Ahmed 34(13) [4s-2 6s-4]
Naman Dhir, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Shahbaz Ahmed to Naman Dhir, 1 run, flatter and sliding in, Dhir tucks it into the mid-wicket pocket
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rohit, no run, quicker and outside off, Rohit sits down to sweep and misses. He was deceived for pace

Shahbaz Ahmed to Rohit, no run, mix-up but Dhir survives. Rohit turns it gently towards square leg and takes a start, Dhir was almost halfway down when he was sent back but Unadkat throws was not on target

Shahbaz Ahmed to Rohit, 2 runs, dropped! Tough chance but should be taken once Samad got there. Short and bounces more, Rohit seeks to pull but gets a thick top-edge and the ball flies over mid-on, Samad runs back and gets both hands but does not hang on. Will this prove to be as costly as the Travis Head drop?
Pat Cummins, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Cummins to Naman Dhir, 1 run, full and angled in, Dhir flicks wide of mid-on and is restricted to a single

Cummins to Rohit, SIX, just over deep mid-wicket. Full and slanting in, right in the slot for Rohit and he whips it towards the vacant deep mid-wicket, 74 meters maximum and one of the smaller ones of the night
Cummins to Rohit, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Cummins to Rohit, out Caught by Abhishek Sharma!! The drop does not cost much. Skipper Cummins strikes and he's delighted. Short of length and right at the batter, Rohit did not have the space to free his arms and hence could not get it off the middle, the top-edge goes towards deep backward square and Abhishek makes no mistake. He keeps his eyes on the ball all the way and takes it safely. Rohit c Abhishek Sharma b Cummins 26(12) [4s-1 6s-3]
Tilak Varma, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Cummins to Tilak Varma, no run, I0$ back of a length angled across, Tilak mistimes the pull towards mid-on
Cummins to Tilak Varma, no run, good length ball around off, Tilak checks his drive and sends it straight to cover
Cummins to Tilak Varma, 1 run, slower ball outside off, Tilak directs it square of the wicket

Highlights (1-5 overs) -> Unadkat goes for 18 runs in his first over -> Kishan punishes Bhuvi - 4,6,6,0,6,1 - 23 runs in an over -> 50 up for Mumbai Indians after 3 overs -> Shahbaz breaks the opening stand, Kishan is gone -> Cummins removes Rohit, he is caught at deep backward square leg
Shahbaz Ahmed to Tilak Varma, byes, 1 run, shuffles across and sits down to play the sweep, but ends up yorking himself and the ball goes through his legs and didn't miss leg-stump by much
Shahbaz Ahmed to Naman Dhir, FOUR, fired full on off-stump, Dhir makes room and lofts inside out over cover, one bounce and over the ropes
Shahbaz Ahmed to Naman Dhir, 1 run, darted into the blockhole, Dhir jams it to mid-on
Shahbaz Ahmed to Tilak Varma, no run, takes a step out and Shahbaz slows it up, Tilak mistimes the drive back to b
Shahbaz Ahmed to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, now goes for the reverse sweep and picks out short third, there's a wayward throw and the pair pick up the extra run
Shahbaz Ahmed to Tilak Varma, 1 run, flatter and short of length, Tilak works it to deep mid-wicket. Just 26 runs from the last 3 overs of the powerplay
Umran Malik, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Highest PP scores for MI in the IPL 84/0 vs DC, Mumbai WS, 2018 83/1 vs SRH, Abu Dhabi, 2021 82/1 vs PBKS, Indore, 2017 78/0 vs CSK, Mumbai WS, 2008 76/2 vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2024
Umran Malik to Tilak Varma, no run, 145.5ks charges down and looks to drive, he's beaten for pace and the ball flies past the outside edge
Malik bowling from round the wicket

Umran Malik to Tilak Varma, 1 run, chance but Klaasen can't hang on. Would have been a stunner. Short and angled down leg, Tilak is late on the pull and the brushes the glove on the way, Klaasen dives full length to his right and parries it to fine leg
Umran Malik to Naman Dhir, wide, slower ball but strays down leg, Dhir can't reach that
Umran Malik to Naman Dhir, SIX, another leg-lined delivery and Dhir connects with this one, uses the pace of Malik and sends it sailing over long leg
Umran Malik to Naman Dhir, 1 run, 146.5ks very full delivery around off, Dhir jams the drive wide of mid-off
Umran Malik to Tilak Varma, no run, 147.9ks full and outside off, Tilak goes hard on the drive and ekes out an inside edge behind to Klaasen
Umran Malik to Tilak Varma, SIX, good end to the over and a much needed six for Tilak. Short and angled in, Tilak swivels and pulls it backward of square, just manages to clear the rope
Mayank Markande, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Markande to Naman Dhir, 1 run, a length ball, pushed slower and was the googly. Dhir late on the pull and skews it down the ground towards long-on after a couple of bounces
Markande to Tilak Varma, SIX, on a length and was the googly again, Varma waits on his backfoot and slap pulls it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum. He's starting to find his feet here...
Markande to Tilak Varma, wide, tries to hide the ball wide outside off. Too wide
Markande to Tilak Varma, 1 run, googly onto off, punched across the line to long-on. 100 up for Mumbai
Markande to Naman Dhir, 1 run, flat delivery onto off, slapped over the bowler's head towards long-off
Markande to Tilak Varma, no run, pushed quicker onto off, was the googly again. Punched towards extra cover
Markande to Tilak Varma, 1 run, dances to the pitch and slams it down to long-off
The physio is out there as Naman Dhir has an issue with his calves. A slight delay
Pat Cummins [1.0-0-8-1] is back into the attack
Cummins to Tilak Varma, FOUR, slower delivery, was pitched up. Varma gets under and chips it over mid-off who was inside the circle. Runs away for four
Cummins to Tilak Varma, wide, slower delivery, too far wide outside off
Cummins to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, back of length and angling across, cut in front of square towards deep extra cover. Two runs taken
Cummins to Tilak Varma, 1 run, off cutter, short of length. Pulled across the line towards deep square
Cummins to Naman Dhir, SIX, top shot!! A back of length slower delivery, angling onto the ribs. Dhir shuffles in and sends it on its way over fine leg for a maximum
Cummins to Naman Dhir, 2 runs, yorker length delivery, clipped softly towards deep mid-wicket
Cummins to Naman Dhir, 1 run, pace off and short, Dhir danced out and wanted to play a big slog across the line. Adjusts as the bowler offers so pace and taps it towards deep mid-wicket

Time-Out. Mumbai staying in the chase, just about. It won't be very encouraging for batters to see that they still need 159 runs after scoring at nearly 13.5 runs an over so far. Let's see how the game progresses.
Stat: MI recorded their fastest team hundred today, off 7.3 overs. They'd got there in 7.1 overs against the same opponent in Abu Dhabi in 2021..
Shahbaz Ahmed [2.0-0-17-1] is back into the attack
Shahbaz Ahmed to Naman Dhir, 1 run, fired in wide outside off, slammed down to long-off
Shahbaz Ahmed to Tilak Varma, SIX, sprayed onto the pads, Varma shuffles in slightly and flicks it over fine leg for a maximum

Shahbaz Ahmed to Tilak Varma, SIX, what a hit!! Switches over like a right hander and then sweeps this length ball over deep point all the way for a maximum. Connected so sweetly with that one, pressure on Shahbaz now
Shahbaz Ahmed to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, darted onto leg stump on a length, tucked towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs

Shahbaz Ahmed to Tilak Varma, SIX, another one!! This game is very cruel on the bowler, Shahbaz errs by floating it up slightly. Tilak Varma wastes no time to give it a big slog sweep over deep mid-wicket
Shahbaz Ahmed to Tilak Varma, 1 run, on a length, punched down to long-on. 22 runs off the over, screws up Shahbaz's figures that was pretty economical till now

Highlights (6-10 overs) -> Umran Malik bowls an expensive over, concedes 15 runs -> 50-run stand up between Tilak and Naman Dhir -> Tilak Verma on the charge, scores 22 runs of the 10th over -> Game on as Mumbai Indians require 137 runs in 10 overs
Jaydev Unadkat [1.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack

Unadkat to Tilak Varma, FOUR, full and wide outside off, Varma gets in line and slams it over extra cover for a boundary. That's a 24-ball 50 for the southpaw Raises his bat and signals towards the dressing room saying 'I got this, I'm in control of the chase'
Unadkat to Tilak Varma, 1 run, on a length sliding onto the pads, tucked to deep mid-wicket

Highest scores after first 10 overs (IPL) 148/2 - SRH vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 141/2 - MI vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2024 131/3 - MI vs SRH, Abu Dhabi, 2021 131/3 - PBKS vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2014 130/0 - Deccan Chargers vs MI, Mumbai DYP, 2008 129/0 - RCB vs PBKS, Bengaluru, 2016

Unadkat to Naman Dhir, FOUR, cute!! Amidst all the bludegeoning of the cricket ball today, there is a place for shots like this too. A length ball wide outside off, Dhir shuffles closer and dabs it between backward point and short third
Unadkat to Naman Dhir, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Unadkat to Naman Dhir, out Caught by Cummins!! Gone! Dances down the wicket to this length ball and slashes it hard but straight towards Cummins at extra cover. The SRH skipper takes a neat reverse cup catch, a much needed wicket for the hosts. They needed to break this partnership! Naman Dhir c Cummins b Unadkat 30(14) [4s-2 6s-2]
Hardik Pandya, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Unadkat to Hardik Pandya, no run, on a length angling onto off from round the wicket, punched towards extra cover
Unadkat to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, off the mark! A length ball angling onto middle and leg, punched down to long-on

What an opportunity this is for Hardik Pandya. He's captaincy appointment has divided opinion and he's not the most popular guy going around at the start of this IPL. But if he can win MI this improbable game, that's a golden ticket to MI immortality!! He revels being the big man for the big occasion, is this his day?
Mayank Markande [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Markande to Hardik Pandya, SIX, smoked!! A tossed up delivery onto middle and off, in the swinging arc for Pandya who slams it over deep mid-wicket
Markande to Hardik Pandya, FOUR, pushed a bit quicker onto off, whacked down the ground to the right of long-off. Just bounces short of the ropes
Markande to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, flat delivery on off, slapped hard towards covers who half stops it, allows the single
Markande to Tilak Varma, no run, pitched fuller and was the googly, Varma rocks back to cut but towards the point fielder
Markande to Tilak Varma, no run, sprayed quicker and outside off, was the googly. Varma can't connect

Markande to Tilak Varma, no ball, 1 run, another googly, Varma rocks back and underedges his big slog towards deep square. Oops, it is a freehit as SRH have only 3 fielders inside the circle. A rookie mistake by a WC winning captain
Markande to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, flat outside off, Pandya slams it hard but there is a fielder at deep extra cover. Just a single, Markande gets away with it
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [2.0-0-28-0] is back into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Hardik Pandya, no run, fuller delivery angling inwards and chasing a backing away Pandya. Defended back to Bhuvi
Bhuvneshwar to Hardik Pandya, no run, superb yorker from Bhuvneshwar!! Danced out but can't get under it, digs it out back towards the bowler
Bhuvneshwar to Hardik Pandya, 2 runs, full delivery on off, driven down the ground and Mayank from long-off slides across and parries it towards long-on
Bhuvneshwar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, fuller length onto the pads, pushed down to long-on. This has been a dream over so far from Bhuvi!
Bhuvneshwar to Tilak Varma, 1 run, good length and angling across, slapped towards deep extra cover.
Bhuvneshwar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, in the blockhole, stabbed down to long-off. Just 5 runs off the over, given the state of the game this is gold dust!!
Markande to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, a leg spinner wide outside off, Pandya throws the kitchen sink at it but slices it slightly. On the bounce to deep cover

Markande to Tilak Varma, SIX, first boundary after 12 balls!! Dances out to the pitch of it and chips in with the line of the ball over wide long-off for a maximum. That ball takes a bit out of Varma's bat, but it was still good enough for six!
100 or more sixes for MI in the IPL 223 - Kieron Pollard 210 - Rohit Sharma 100 - Hardik Pandya
Markande to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, pushed quicker onto leg stump, turned towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs
Markande to Tilak Varma, 1 run, wide outside off, Varma gets closer and punches it towards sweeper cover
Markande to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, length ball outside off, punched hard but towards long-off
Markande to Tilak Varma, 1 run, dances out and tries to get under it, but Markande pushed it quicker. Drilled down to long-on

Time-out. 96 off the last 6 overs, this will be one of the greatest chases in T20 history if MI can somehow pull it off. The good news is the pitch is their friend, this is still a very good batting surface. SRH need just one good over, or a break in the partnership. It is their game to lose, hang on for a thrilling finale!
Pat Cummins [2.0-0-25-1] is back into the attack
Cummins to Tilak Varma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Cummins to Tilak Varma, out Caught by Mayank!! Break in play and that yields a wicket!! And it is cricket's golden boy Pat Cummins who gets the breakthrough. A back of length slower delivery onto off, Varma got closer to pull it across the line. Skews his timing and Mayank from long-on runs forward and makes no mistake. The set batter is gone for MI!! Tilak Varma c Mayank b Cummins 64(34) [4s-2 6s-6]
Tim David, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Cummins to Tim David, no run, 143.4 clicks, full and angling onto the boots. Clipped towards mid-wicket
Cummins to Tim David, 1 run, pace off and hits the deck hard, pulled into the ground towards deep square
Cummins to Hardik Pandya, no run, superb yorker from Cummins, stabbed back to him by Hardik.
Cummins to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, slower ball, back of length on off. Swiped across the line to deep mid-wicket
STAT: The highest target successfully chased in a Men's T20 game is 259 by South Africa against West Indies in Centurion last year (with 7 balls remaining).
Cummins to Tim David, 1 run, on a length on off, pulled towards deep backward square leg. Just 3 runs off the over, is this the spell that tilts the game?

Highlights (11-15 overs) -> Unadkat breaks the 3rd wicket partnership, removes Naman Dhir -> Hardik hits a six and boundary against Markande, keeps the scoreboard ticking -> Bhuvi bowls an economical over, executes his yorkers -> Cummins strikes after the time-out, Tilak is caught at long-on -> Mumbai Indians require 93 runs off 5 overs
Jaydev Unadkat [2.0-0-28-1] is back into the attack
Unadkat to Tim David, no run, full outside off, David hits it into the pitch and towards the keeper
Unadkat to Tim David, 1 run, pace off and length on off, David with a big swipe across the line that goes tamely towards deep square
Unadkat to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, length ball outside off, slammed down the ground to long-off, MI need the fours and sixes!
Unadkat to Tim David, no run, slower delivery outside off, was back of a length. Surprises David who has to wait a long time and then taps it tamely to the right of the keeper
Unadkat to Tim David, wide, length ball outside off, was very wide and the umpire calls it. SRH review but it will remain a wide
Unadkat to Tim David, 1 run, pace off and full outside off, slammed across the line towards deep mid-wicket
Unadkat to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, short ball just outside off, pulled uppishly but on the bounce towards deep square leg. Another superb over for SRH, this game is totally slipping away from MI now
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [3.0-0-33-0] is back into the attack

Bhuvneshwar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, yorker length delivery, Pandya stayed deep in his crease and tried to get under it. Hoists it towards long-on, on the bounce to Markram who does well to get his body behind it
Bhuvneshwar to Tim David, 2 runs, short ball, David backed away to pull it away but towards deep mid-wicket. Just a couple
Bhuvneshwar to Tim David, SIX, first six in 20 balls!! A full delivery angling onto the pads, David clears his front leg and flicks it over deep backward square leg for a maximum!
Bhuvneshwar to Tim David, FOUR, short ball outside off, David goes for a big backhand slash and gets a top edge that flies over the keeper for a boundary
Bhuvneshwar to Tim David, SIX, unreal power from Tim David!! A tennis backhand slash that sails over deep extra cover for a maximum. He's striking them cleanly now
Bhuvneshwar to Tim David, 1 run, yorker length delivery, well executed by Bhuvi. Drilled down to long-off
Unadkat to Tim David, FOUR, pace off and full outside off. David waits and then smokes it down the ground for a boundary. To the right of the bowler and hit with great power
Unadkat to Tim David, 1 run, in the blockhole outside off, stabbed out to deep extra cover

Unadkat to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, superb fielding!! A slower bouncer outside off, Pandya slaps it hard across the line. Gets plenty of elevation and gets the distance as well. A surreal attempt by Mayank who jumps up from long-on to grab the ball metres away from the ropes, and throw it back into play as he fell over. Hurts himself in the process, but saves 5 runs for his side. The entire stadium applauds the effort, and Agarwal is fit to continue.
Unadkat to Tim David, wide, too wide outside off, angling away outside off

Unadkat to Tim David, SIX, take that!! A big slog across the line by big Tim David that sails over deep mid-wicket. First time Unadkat angles it straighter, and he gets punished. That's now 500 runs in the game, first time ever in the IPL
Unadkat to Tim David, 1 run, slower bouncer, David dabs it towards backward point
Unadkat to Hardik Pandya, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Unadkat to Hardik Pandya, out Caught by Klaasen!! Gone!! Hardik might have to wait a bit longer to win over a few of his MI fans. A cutter outside off, was back of length and offered no pace. Pandya takes a big swipe at it and toe-ends it in the air towards the keeper. Walks away a bit grumpily, Unadkat has a wry smile on his face. Hardik Pandya c Klaasen b Unadkat 24(20) [4s-1 6s-1]
Impact sub: Romario Shepherd comes IN for Maphaka
Romario Shepherd, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Pat Cummins [3.0-0-28-2] is back into the attack
Cummins to Tim David, 1 run, hard length ball, pulled powerfully but towards deep square. Just a single
Cummins to Shepherd, 1 run, slower bouncer, Shepherd shuffles in and pulls towards deep square leg. Just a single!!
Cummins to Tim David, 2 runs, short of length at just 120.6 clicks, David underedges his big pull shot towards deep backward square leg
Cummins to Tim David, no run, hard length delivery, bounces over David's attempted pull shot. He reviews for height, but that's fine. Legal delivery
Cummins to Tim David, 2 runs, bowls the heavy ball into the pitch, David takes a wild swipe at it and skies it up in the air. Lands safely towards mid-wicket
Cummins to Tim David, 1 run, back of length delivery, pulled towards deep backward square leg. Just a single
Mayank Markande [3.0-0-37-0] is back into the attack
Markande to Tim David, 1 run, flat delivery onto off, slammed down to long-off
Markande to Shepherd, SIX, floated up outside off, Shepherd waits and then tonks it straight down the ground. Six number 38 off the game, the most ever in a T20 game!!
Markande to Shepherd, no run, flat delivery outside off, Shepherd swings blind and misses
Markande to Shepherd, FOUR, flat outside off, Shepherd shuffles inwards and slams it down the ground. To the right of long-off for a four
Markande to Shepherd, FOUR, flat outside off, Shepherd stays back and cuts it square for a boundary
Markande to Shepherd, no run, flat delivery outside off, Shepherd can't connect on the swing. SRH win by 31 runs, the trend of home wins in the IPL continues!!

23:19 Local Time, 17:49 GMT, 23:19 IST: What a wild game of cricket!! The 35,000 or so at the stadium are a part of a historic game, a T20 game with the most sixes ever and the most runs scored collectively. Let the margin of defeat not deceive you, because this game was a lot closer till the second strategic time-out. Mumbai Indians got off to a solid start, as Rohit Sharma went on the attack against Jaydev Unadkat, while Kishan took down Bhuvneshwar Kumar from the other end. The openers got to 56 after just 3.2 overs, before Kishan holed out to Shahbaz. Rohit followed him shortly, as he skewed his pull shot against a Pat Cummins bouncer. Mumbai however rebuild with Naman Dhir and Tilak Varma, as the two youngsters played aggressive cricket to keep the asking rate in check. Varma attacked the spinners, scoring sixes for fun to get a fifty. However, the SRH skipper Cummins returned after the time-out, and got the much needed wicket of the southpaw. Hardik and Tim David huffed and puffed after, but SRH's pacers were superb - hiding the ball outside off and offering no pace. The chase never took shape after that, as MI lose their second game as well. Stick around for the presentations.

Travis Head: Feeling good, the batting team has done an exceptional job in the last two games, feels good to contribute. It was very enjoyable tonight. We were aggressive in the first game as well, that's one thing we want to do at the top. I am pleased I could target both the off-side and leg-side. Earlier I would just target the leg side. It's a great blueprint for us moving forward. Haven't spoken to Tim David yet. You just try to sum up the conditions well. I was pleased how things worked out in the powerplay. They (MI) got so much power and experience as well. With 280-odd, I felt we had enough.

Hardik Pandya: Not really (thought SRH would score 277 at the toss). Wicket was good, 277 no matter how bad or good you bowl, if the opposition has to score that much, they have batted well. They (the bowlers) were good, it was tough out there, almost 500 runs were scored and the wicket was helping the batters, we could have done a few things here and there, but having said that, we have a young bowling attack and we will learn. If the ball goes this many times into the crowd, you will need time to get the overs done. Everyone (the batters) looked good and it is just a matter of time before we put things right. He (Kwena Maphaka) was fantastic, coming into his first game and getting overwhelmed, he was alright and backed his skillset, just needs some game time.

- Today was the first instance of four bowlers conceding 50-plus runs in an IPL match.

Pat Cummins: That was insane. The ball was really pinging around. Not until we bowled, it got a bit too close for comfort. They found a boundary whenever they needed it, but we finished it off well. (On Abhishek Sharma) Really impressive, in IPL you play with a lot of pressure but he plays with great freedom. (On plans in first innings) You never play for 270, but we wanted to be postive and be aggressive, take the game on. It was a good wicket, so we have to suck it up knowing we would go for a few boundaries. What's important is to have clear plans with the ball. (On home crowd) Amazing atmosphere in the ground, enjoyed playing here, was incredibly loud.

Abhishek Sharma | Player of the Match: I said in the previous interview too, the domestic season gives us a lot of confidence. The message for the batters is simple - go out and express yourself. The plan was to attack, I enjoyed batting with Head, he's one of my favourite batters, I admire him. He told me to go for it if it was in my zone. I'm happy to be getting my chances, doesn't matter what position I'm playing. I had a chance to talk to Brian Lara last night, that helped me massively. I would rather bowl more in practice than bat, trying my best with bowling as well.

Fortunately, this happened on a cricket field because otherwise some of these batters today could be charged with I0$, for the way they bludgeoned the bowlers today. It started with Travis Heads fastest fifty for SRH, which was usurped by Abhishek Sharma in a matter of balls. And then the two South Africans showed no mercy to the MI bowlers, with Klaasen scoring 80 off just 34 balls. MI kept in line of the chase as the top four of Rohit, Kishan, Varma and Naman Dhir all smashed sixes for fun. However, at the end of the day 277 runs were a bit too many.

Life comes at you fast if you are Hardik Pandya. Last year this time, he had his feet up captaining a champion franchise. But he chose a different route for himself by getting traded back to Mumbai, splitting the whole fan base right down the middle. He revels being cricket’s pantomime villain, and now he’s had two games where he could have been the hero in the chase but walked off begrudgingly in the final over after failing on both occasions. Not quite the homecoming he would have expected, but there are still 12 more group games and MI have never been fast starters. Time to rest those thumbs after this exhausting day at the office. This is I0$ signing off on behalf on I1$ and I2$
